                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/5634: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Casablanca</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Goold</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Casablanca</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-09-23T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 23, 1940—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 23—4:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>136. A German port commission of five members arrived today for a visit of 2 days
                    after which they will proceed to Dakar.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Goold</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
